Lines.LineContent: ANNUAL REPORT of SALMON STREAMS and SPAWNING POPULATION
SPAWNING RUN TIMING and ESTIMATED NUMBER
(A) Enhancement activities or intense biological activities.
(C) Obstructions or changes in habitat with recommendations.
(D) Large variation in sex ratio or unusual number of jacks.
(E) High/low water flow level during spawning.
(A) Evidence of erosion and silting. Give extent or percent of stream bed affected:
A small amount of blowdown in the lower sections, with some further minor course changes.
(B) Particulars of scouring of spawning beds or change in course of stream :
The upper log jam has built up, and was impassable throughout the spawning period.
(C) Water levels flow, normal, abnormal. If abnormal, details should be given :
Consistently good water levels through the spawning period. Flooding during the last two weeks of October.
(D) Particulars of distribution of salmon over stream bed :
Up to log jam at 1.2 km.
Moderate impact from birds and bears.
(F) Evidence of digging up eggs by late spawning fish :
The upper log jam must be monitored in future years. If the jam does not get removed by winter floods, (unlikely), some chainsaw work could be contemplated.
